<TITLE> Sheikh Selim, Babar, Mirza Abbas get bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 15 (bdnews24.com)  The High Court has granted former ministers Sheikh Fazlul Karim Selim, Lutfozzaman Babar and Mirza Abbas bail for three months. The vacation bench of justices Mirza Hossain Haider and Mamnun Rahman in the orders also asked the government to explain why the case proceedings against them should not be declared illegal. The court also granted bail to Afroza Abbas, wife of Mirza Abbas, former BNP housing and public works minister. Sheikh Selim was health minister in 1996-2001 Hasina administration and Babr state minister for home in 2001-2006 Khaleda cabinet. Anticorruption Commission filed the cases against the former lawmakers for amassing wealth beyond their known sources of income. The case against Sheikh Selim was filed with Ramna police on Apr 23, 2007. Selim was picked up by police on May 23. Former minister Abbas and former state minister Babar were arrested on Feb 25 and May 28 respectively. In another development the Supreme Court upheld High Court bail orders for former BNP lawmakers Nasiruddin Ahmed Pintu, Salauddin Ahmed, and businessman Nur Ali but overturned the stay orders on the separate case proceedings against them. bdne
